This is a very good weekday recipe. It is quick, easy to make and very tasty. One addition I made was to add a grilled and chopped chicken breast.

Rating: 3
This came out great, but I made a few changes. I replaced onions with shallots and added some grated lemon peel. I also used homemade chicken broth. And I had some fresh sheep's milk cheese so I stirred some of that in at the end. I also normally don't add most of the liquid in the beginning of a risotto, but for this one it seems helpful to do so to incorporate all the Swiss chard. I didn't measure it, but I probably had more than 4 cups of chard and a rather small pan so the liquid helped wilt it fast so I could get it all in.

Rating: 3
This was a great way to use up chard. I would make it again. I think maybe next time I would look into adding garlic or some other spice.

Rating: 4
I used rainbow chard and made a couple of minor modifications to the recipe. I diced the stems of the chard and cooked them with the onion. I also stirred in a tablespoon of butter at the end with the cheese. Served as a side dish with a beef tenderloin roast with a Creole spice rub. The dish was visually appealing and delicious.

Rating: 2
This recipe needed something more, it was a little unexciting. I also felt like the chard got overcooked. Next time I might add some of the chard stems at the beginning and then save the leaved to add near the end.

