Rating: 4
Made this for tonight's main course... I was a bit doubtful, I was worried it would be bland, but it turned out really well. I used white chard, added 2 cloves of coarsely chopped garlic and a bit of freshly ground white pepper, and used homemade chicken stock. I also added a knob of butter at the end with the cheese. Really yummy. Have made lots of risotto and tried many different recipes... this one ties for first place. A german Mosel Riesling was a great pairing. Dinner tonight: success! :)

